---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="CV" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5 flex items-center justify-between flex-wrap gap-3">
    <div class="text-3xl font-bold">Profile</div>
    <!-- Drop your CV PDF in /public as cv.pdf so this link works. -->
    <a href="/cv.pdf" target="_blank" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline">Download CV (PDF)</a>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    PhD student in Electrical &amp; Computer Engineering at the University of Houston, with a mathematics
    background (M.S., Shenzhen University). My research applies deep learning to geophysical and environmental
    imaging — probabilistic airborne electromagnetic (AEM) inversion, hyperspectral methane detection, and
    underwater image processing — alongside current work on CO2 / CCS subsurface monitoring.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="PhD, Electrical & Computer Engineering"
      subtitle="Aug 2024 to Present at University of Houston, Houston, TX, USA"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="M.S., Mathematics & Applied Mathematics"
      subtitle="Sept 2021 to Jun 2024 at Shenzhen University, Shenzhen, China"
    >
      <!-- Class ranking 1/28 (2022–2023). Tencent Founder Scholarship (top 1%) and first-class scholarship (top 10%). -->
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="B.S., Mathematics & Applied Mathematics"
      subtitle="Sept 2017 to Jul 2021 at Guangzhou University, Guangzhou, China"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Research experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant — MODAL Lab (advisor: Dr. Jiefu Chen)"
      subtitle="Aug 2024 to Present at University of Houston, Houston, TX, USA"
    >
      Deep learning for geophysical imaging: probabilistic AEM inversion with conditional variational
      autoencoders, and CO2 / CCS monitoring with 4D seismic and gravity.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant (advisor: Dr. Qianqian Tong)"
      subtitle="Aug 2023 to Jan 2024 at Pengcheng Laboratory, Shenzhen, China"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant (advisor: Dr. Bo Chen)"
      subtitle="Oct 2021 to Jun 2023 at Shenzhen University, Shenzhen, China"
    />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Assistant (advisor: Dr. Yubin Zhong)"
      subtitle="Aug 2018 to Sept 2018 at Guangzhou University, Guangzhou, China"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Publications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-2 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      C. Zhou, S. Wu, J. Sun, J. Chen, Y. Huang, "Probabilistic inversion of airborne electromagnetic data using
      a conditional variational autoencoder: Yellowstone case study," <i>IEEE Transactions on Geoscience and
      Remote Sensing</i> (accepted).
    </li>
    <li>
      C. Zhou, S. Wu, J. Sun, J. Chen, Y. Huang, "Deep learning-based probabilistic imaging of Yellowstone's
      hydrothermal system from AEM data," <i>AGU Annual Meeting</i>, 2025 (abstract).
    </li>
    <li>
      Y. Zi, C. Zhou, J. Chen, Z. Han, Y. Huang, X. Wu, "Hyperspectral methane plume segmentation through
      foundation computer vision models," <i>IEEE Access</i>.
    </li>
    <li>
      B. Chen, C. Zhou*, X. Sun, "Enhancing green screen matting with group normalization and perceptual loss
      for color overflow and complex edges," <i>The Visual Computer</i>.
    </li>
    <li>
      C. Zhou, L. Walker, X. Fu, J. Chen, Y. Huang, X. Wu, "A mobile platform for AI-powered underwater image
      processing," <i>Offshore Technology Conference (OTC)</i>, 2025.
    </li>
    <li>
      C. Zhou, B. Chen, Y. Zhang, W. Chen, B. Pan, J. Ji, "Underwater image enhancement via multi-color space
      correction and fusion," <i>ICEIECT</i>, 2023.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <div class="mx-6 mb-10 text-sm opacity-75">
    * corresponding author ·
    <a class="underline" href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=9xZXl44AAAAJ&hl=en" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Awards &amp; honors</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>Tencent Founder Scholarship (top 0.6%), 2023</li>
    <li>First-class graduate scholarship (top 10%), 2022 &amp; 2023</li>
    <li>Second prize, APMCM Mathematical Contest in Modeling (top 30%), 2022</li>
    <li>Research Excellence Prize for Undergraduates (top 30%), 2021</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
